The Minister of the FCT, Malam Muhammad Musa Bello, has offered his condolences to the governor of Adamawa State, Alhaji Ahmadu Umar Fintiri and the entire people of the state on the passing of Hajia Fatima Umar Badami, mother of the governor. A statement signed by the minister’s Chief Press Secretary, Mr. Anthony Ogunleye, described the late Hajia Fatima Badami, as a pillar of her community, whose strong moral and religious convictions impacted positively on all those who had the honour of knowing her. He asked the governor and all members of his immediate and extended family and indeed the entire people of Adamawa State to take solace in the fact the Hajia Fatima Badami lived a worthy and exemplary life and prayed that the Almighty Allah (SWT) grants her   eternal rest in Jannatul Firdaus.  6 governors at Gusau’s wife’s burial Education minister, Adamu Adamu loses mother Adamawa governor, Fintiri loses mother